"very satisfied with their operation" (p = 0.07). Complication rates were 
similar, and a single recurrence, in a patient in the OH group, has been 
observed after a median follow-up of 14 months.
CONCLUSIONS: Direct cost measurements showed LH to be 40% more expensive than OH 
in the context of a Canadian-type health care system. To date, benefits in 
postoperative pain and possibly quality of life have been detected in the LH 
