patients with 1, 2-3, > 3 hepatic nodules was 29, 21 and 17% respectively (p < 
0.05). 4) The extent of surgical resection: 5-year survival after minor and 
major resection was 28 and 18% respectively (p < 0.05). At multivariate analysis 
only stage of primary and percentage of hepatic replacement retained statistical 
significance. In 60% of 154 patients with recurrent disease the liver was again 
involved.

